.TH "pcm_close" 9 "pcm_close" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcm_close \- implements close callback function for PCM middle layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcm_close
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
sub-stream pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Obviously, this is called when a PCM substream is closed. Any private
instance for a PCM substream allocated in the open callback will be
released here.

Returns 0 on success or error code otherwise.
